] Remember, this is what Yosef intends to communicate: Although until now we've done EB3 Visa's because it gets the candidates a Green Card, the problem is the timelines on that were always long, but are getting longer and longer to where most clients avoid. moving forward we are likely to focus much more on TN Visa's as they are nearly immediate and super useful (but only available for Canadians and Mexicans)\\n[Fri 2026-03-27 08:50 GMT+2] I really hope you are taking active notes now because this pushback I am giving you is something you should know how to do with NavaAA.I am leaning towards 2. but it's not immediately clear what we are talking about or who we are talking to.\\n[Fri 2026-03-27 10:10 GMT+2] Discuss that with your agent. Remember, I want to discuss somewhere in this article the differences, the costs, the delays and realities on the ground, the forecasts, etc. I still need a narrative arc that ends with how Nava can become an invaluable partner that could run both simultaneously to address both your short-term gaping holes and long-term stability. Do not be shy to refer to the last article because we are not contradicting it. Makes sense?\\nThe system is grinding to a halt. PERM at 16-17 months becomes \\\"longer than most RN orientations.\\\" India EB-3 frozen at 2013 becomes \\\"a nurse who started her PERM in 2012 is still waiting.\\\" Data as visceral countdown, not academic footnote.\\n[Fri 2026-03-27 10:25 GMT+2] Why is your option A alternating between H2 and H3s? Remember I need 3-4 H2s and under each should be at least 3 H3s? Give me the proposed H2s only and a brief narrative arc. Either way, I am quite interested in option B but do contine to refine this, I will be back in about 15 minutes so use all the time to do something productive!\\n[Fri 2026-03-27 10:43 GMT+2] I am back and I am strongly considering Option B because the is the first time we are discussing this on the blog and this is a better intro. One note though, H2.3, the forec