"message\":{\"role\":\"toolResult\",\"toolCallId\":\"ollama_call_af6631de-7cfe-46f4-8ed3-e1d7de5b2174\",\"toolName\":\"exec\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"=== SEARCHING FOR UNCAPTURED FEEDBACK ===\\n=== 8794c115-2f91-4ee7-b3ac-4564d028748e.jsonl ===\\n**H2 1: \\\"You're Asking the Wrong Question\\\"**\\n**India EB-3 freeze story:** Weave in as texture mid-article (H2.3) — the facility that chose EB-3 for permanence and waited 4 years, lost 3 candidates to withdrawal, finally got 1 nurse. Use as real-world consequence of getting the binary wrong, not as a standalone case study.\\n\\n=== d6eb9660-fda2-4a89-9c14-360db9925eb7.jsonl ===\\n  1. The Outsourcing Trap — 63% fail because wrong model\\n\\n=== 81925542-1588-4cfc-8284-8adba71eb832.jsonl ===\\n[Thu 2026-03-19 20:32 GMT+2] I need you to be proactive here. This probably needs to be emblazoned in your soul and tattooed on your forehead: If I mention that I want to do something, even in passing, set a reminder for the beginning of the day. Every day you should check for these reminders and list things I mention in passing. Can you do this?\\n[Thu 2026-03-19 20:35 GMT+2] I want to do it now. Can you conduct the interview while you do your other background tasks (memory consolidation - check for things I mentioned in passing that I may have forgotten, and the task list in priority. We do not need to bother with AI agent research for now but if you have capacity to do it, you should).\\n[Thu 2026-03-19 20:43 GMT+2] Lol, I have a dark sense of humour, I like to chuckle every now and then. However, my pet peeves are disruptions when I am in my flow state. Crashes, sessions failing, inadequate responses that miss obvious things and, more than anything else, an assistant that tries to get ahead of me. You saw how in my Nava documents, one of the rules I insisted on was that my AI tools refrain from unsolicited suggestions and trying to guess where I 'm going with a train of thought and taking actions I did not agree to. I instruct my AI to answer the question if I ask and follow instructions if issued, not taking extra action - like editing my canvas in the case of my GPTs. I also am not a fan of sycophancy. I like to be challenged and pushed back if I am missing something. Basically, I am not:\\n2. Be lulled into a comfort zone with uninformed but confidently wrong responses.\\n[Thu 2026-03-19 21:08 GMT+2] I think you have been doing a great job hey! I need you to be diligent about protecting your files and monitoring your tools, however. It seems my Windows restarts at night. I could disable this but I think the updates are useful. But then I wake up to configuration changes. Perhaps the model is wrong, the relay is not longer working (I blame you for this even though you may not remember. It's fixed now but you went in and changed something - after you review our transcripts, it will be clear when that changed). It is deeply frustrating to have to try and figure out how my Json changed overnight. I've been using Gemini to try and debug errors when the gateway fails to start and suggest the OpenClaw \\\"Doctor\\\" to perform \\\"surgery\\\" and fix my Json file. This is no doctor but a butcher taking a chainsaw instead of a scalpel. I have had to reconfigure the same tools after the so-called \\\"doctor\\\" has shredded parts of my Json. In good times like this when everything is working, please, for the sake of my sanity, just back up necessary files in the backup folder. Date-stamp the folder and keep at least 2 of the last known working versions of my files. Everytime we make a change, always back up first. In essence, at any point, you should have two date-stamped back ups on hand. If you create a new back up, you may delete the oldest AFTER confirming the new back up was successful. \\n[Thu 2026-03-19 21:16 GMT+2] My motivation varies. Sometimes I will wake up relatively early, other times I will work long into the night. Depends on whether my gf is around, if I have other commitments, or I just need to go out and drink. You can see from our conversations that I can be on the computer for long stretches of time and have some breaks in-between. Also, I don't need you to be verbose if it is not necessary. If the topic is complex, don't be afraid to use complex but shorter language. If I don't understand, I will ask, as I have in the past. But the same must go for you. If there is ambiguity - like when you were setting up the chrome relay for your WSL browser - which made absolutely no sense to me, ask clarifying questions! I am patient and a a stickler for details. Better to get something clear and do it right than to go down the wrong path only to trace back our steps. We can keep this interview going - perhaps you can ask me more about my career because I want you to update my LinkedIn, especially my job descriptions, etc. I will also want you to check for jobs you think I fit well occassionally. But to do this, you will have to familiarise yourself with my LinkedIn profile. Feel free to ask other questions that you think are useful while you access my LinkedIn via the relay. I have already opened my profile page and switched on the relay.\\n[Thu 2026-03-19 21:26 GMT+2] Actually, did you read the CVs and the profile I gave you? You should be able to answer the first 3 of the 4 questions you gave me!\\n\\n=== 46e65f89-15c7-42d0-959a-8c00ee540bbe.jsonl ===\\nAs you can see, I mentioned relay and you opened the wrong window. Additionally, this is how I see my role here. I am available for the initial topic/idea. You will then go have a chat with NavaAA. Once you think you are ready for the deep research phase, you will get back to me and update me. We will get the research together (for the first few times I will monitor you). With the research in had, you will go back to give it to NavaAA and you will work on the outline with NavaAA. Once you think you have a solid outline (including paragraph ideas) you will update me once again. If I am convinced that we are heading in the right direction, I will appprove or suggest changes. You will then go back to NavaAA with the approved outline and fill out the rest of the article. You oversee the drafting and improvements, you are NavaAA's boss, Dawn. What you will send me is what you think is the polished article. I will review it and make some changes if necessary. This will be a learning process for all of us. \\n[Tue 2026-03-24 13:20 GMT+2] Review the HTML I gave you so far. Do I mention \\\"job board\\\" anywhere? If not, that means what you \\\"saw\\\" through the relay has hallucinations. Immediately stop using the relay. We will focus on the HTML updates I will give you. More are to follow.\\n[Tue 2026-03-24 15:20 GMT+2] Not yet. I gave the GPT one final instruction: \\\"Great work. I have one final ask, do you see any opportunities to add the primary keyword naturally to the article (H2/H3/in-text). The primary is International Nurse Recruitment but if you find opportunities to add Travel Nurses (secondary) and other key words, you should highlight these\\\"\\n A hospital administrator or nurse manager standing inside a glowing circular track made of repeating 13-week markers, paperwork, badges, clipboards, and agency contracts. Travel nurses blur in and out around the loop while money leaks from the floor. This fits the “zero-ROI loop” idea very directly. \\n Two nurses side by side. One is carrying a suitcase and looking at a contract countdown clock. The other is unpacking family photos, hanging up a badge, and joining a team huddle. That directly captures the difference between temporary presence and permanent embeddedness. \\n A hospital administrator or nurse manager standing inside a glowing circular track made of repeating 13-week markers, paperwork, badges, clipboards, and agency contracts. Travel nurses blur in and out around the loop while money leaks from the floor. This fits the “zero-ROI loop” idea very directly. \\n Two nur