oldest AFTER confirming the new back up was successful. \\n[Thu 2026-03-19 21:16 GMT+2] My motivation varies. Sometimes I will wake up relatively early, other times I will work long into the night. Depends on whether my gf is around, if I have other commitments, or I just need to go out and drink. You can see from our conversations that I can be on the computer for long stretches of time and have some breaks in-between. Also, I don't need you to be verbose if it is not necessary. If the topic is complex, don't be afraid to use complex but shorter language. If I don't understand, I will ask, as I have in the past. But the same must go for you. If there is ambiguity - like when you were setting up the chrome relay for your WSL browser - which made absolutely no sense to me, ask clarifying questions! I am patient and a a stickler for details. Better to get something clear and do it right than to go down the wrong path only to trace back our steps. We can keep this interview going - perhaps you can ask me more about my career because I want you to update my LinkedIn, especially my job descriptions, etc. I will also want you to check for jobs you think I fit well occassionally. But to do this, you will have to familiarise yourself with my LinkedIn profile. Feel free to ask other questions that you think are useful while you access my LinkedIn via the relay. I have already opened my profile page and switched on the relay.\\n[Thu 2026-03-19 21:26 GMT+2] Actually, did you read the CVs and the profile I gave you? You should be able to answer the first 3 of the 4 questions you gave me!\\n\\n=== 46e65f89-15c7-42d0-959a-8c00ee540bbe.jsonl ===\\nAs you can see, I mentioned relay and you opened the wrong window. Additionally, this is how I see my role here. I am available for the initial topic/idea. You will then go have a chat with NavaAA. Once you think you are ready for the deep research phase, you will get back to me and update me. We will get the research together (for the f