assistant that tries to get ahead of me. You saw how in my Nava documents, one of the rules I insisted on was that my AI tools refrain from unsolicited suggestions and trying to guess where I 'm going with a train of thought and taking actions I did not agree to. I instruct my AI to answer the question if I ask and follow instructions if issued, not taking extra action - like editing my canvas in the case of my GPTs. I also am not a fan of sycophancy. I like to be challenged and pushed back if I am missing something. Basically, I am not:\\n1. Looking to outsource my thinking but to enhance it\\n2. Be lulled into a comfort zone with uninformed but confidently wrong responses.\\n```json\\n{\\n  \\\"label\\\": \\\"openclaw-tui (gateway-client)\\\",\\n  \\\"id\\\": \\\"gateway-client\\\",\\n  \\\"name\\\": \\\"openclaw-tui\\\",\\n  \\\"username\\\": \\\"openclaw-tui\\\"\\n}\\n```\\n[Thu 2026-03-19 20:48 GMT+2] I need to master Openclaw and similar tools, like Agent Zero. I have a limited budget and basically a shit computer tbh. (I mean it's alright for 90% of people but my current interests around AI might require a meaner machine. And yes, I follow football, primarily Arsenal, as well as F1. I have Arsenal on my calendar, as do I have F1. However, sometimes there are really interesting matches across Europe worth watching. Barca played Newcastle yesterday, as did Man City with Real Madrid. Those are matches I watched but did not appear on my calendar - a heads up when there is an interesting upcoming fixture would be nice.\\n```json\\n{\\n  \\\"label\\\": \\\"openclaw-tui (gateway-client)\\\",\\n  \\\"id\\\": \\\"gateway-client\\\",\\n  \\\"name\\\": \\\"openclaw-tui\\\",\\n  \\\"username\\\": \\\"openclaw-tui\\\"\\n}\\n```\\n[Thu 2026-03-19 21:08 GMT+2] I think you have been doing a great job hey! I need you to be diligent about protecting your files and monitoring your tools, however. It seems my Windows restarts at night. I could disable this but I think the update